"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nMariana A. Pimentel June 28, 1911 - July 24, 2009 Resident of San Mateo Passed away in San Mateo on July 24, 2009. Beloved wife of the late Manuel Pimentel. Dear sister of Maria Araujo of San Mateo, Irene Arruda of Sacramento, and the late Manuel Arruda, Argenio Arruda, and Jose Arruda. She was the loving sister-in-law of Honorina Arruda of San Mateo, Marie Arruda of Modesto, and the late Doris Arruda. Also survivived by many loving nieces and nephews. Mariana was born in Fall River, MA and was a resident of San Mateo for 50 years. A Funeral Mass will be celebrated at 10:00 a.m. on Tuesday, July 28, 2009 at St. Gregory Catholic Church, 28th and Hacienda Street in San Mateo. Committal at Holy Cross Cemetery in Colma. SNEIDER &amp; SULLIVAN &amp; O'CONNELL'S FUNERAL HOME (650) 343-1804\n</p>\n<p>\nPublished in East Bay Times on July 28, 2009 - See more at: http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/eastbaytimes/obituary.aspx?n=mariana-a-pimentel&amp;pid=130507765#sthash.SZ7mSh1u.dpuf\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
