"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nHe married Maria C\u00e2ndida, daughter of<br />\nManuel Ant\u00f3nio de Vasconcelos and Ana da Concei\u00e7\u00e3o Amoreira, on 25 Mar 1836 in the Ermida de Nossa Senhora do Pilar. She<br />\nwas born on 20 Mar 1820 in Pilar where she died on 2 Dec 1910 in Pilar. (NB: Possibly the foundling baptized in Bretanha on 20 Mar 1820<br />\nand fostered by Inacio Cabral (sic)  (Medeiros) and Ana Joaquina. She was actually the illegitimate child of Ana da  Concei\u00e7\u00e3o and Manuel<br />\nAnt\u00f3nio Vasconcelos, founder of the A\u00e7oreano Oriental and co-founder of O Tempo. [See Os A\u00e7ores atrav\u00e9s algumas figuras e epis\u00f3dios<br />\nde uma \u00c9poca.  Lisbon: 1979 and Manuel Ferreira, Manuel Ant\u00f3nio de Vasconcelos: o 1\u00ba Jornalista Micaelense e O A\u00e7oreano Oriental.<br />\nEdi\u00e7\u00e3o Impra\u00e7or, Lda. Ponta Delgada: 1994. Manuel Ferreira says that Breno Dias de Vasconcelos reports her birth (sic) as 9 Jul 1820, but           this is probably a typographical error as there is no foundling baptized in Bretanha at this time.<br />\nShe is Maria Ricarda on son Manuel's birth record and Maria Ricarda de Jesus on her death record. Reported to be 90 years old on her\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
