"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nFALL RIVER--Manuel C. \"Albino\" Carvalho, 76, of Covel Street died Tuesday, March 11, 1997, at Charlton Memorial Hospital after a short illness. He was the husband of Emiliana (Diogo) Carvalho and son of the late Jose and Sarina dos Anjos (Sousa) Carvalho.\n</p>\n<p>\nBorn in Ajuda Bretanha, St. Michael, Azores, Mr. Carvalho came to Fall River in 1965. A retired construction worker, he also worked for several years at Whaling Manufacturing Co. in Fall River. A parishioner of Espirito Santo Church, he was a member of the Our Lady of Light Society.\n</p>\n<p>\nSurvivors include his widow; four sons, Joseph Carvalho of Westport, Manuel Carvalho of Tulare, Calif.; Antonio Carvalho of Riverdale, Calif.; and Leonardo Carvalho of Fall River; three daughters, Natalie Cordeiro of Fall River, Mary Silva of Freetown and Mary Lou Farias of Bakersfield, Calif.; two sisters, Guilhermina Carvalho of St. Michael, Azores, and Conceicao Brazil of Toronto, Canada; 16 grandchildren; a great-granddaughter; and several nieces and nephews.\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nDesaparecido no Calhau dos Rem\u00e9dios a 30 de Mar\u00e7o 1925, levado pelo mar o seu cad\u00e1ver<br />\nApareceu no Morro das Capelas a 13 de Mar\u00e7o 1925\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
