"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nHe died in the earthquake of Vila Franca\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nHe came to S.Miguel from Madeira and lived in Ponta Gar\u00e7a.\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nNotas Gerais: Mandou construir a Ermida da M\u00e3e de Deus em Ponta Delgada,  foi o primeiro morador de Vila Franca, depois foi residente em Ponta Delgada, onde ele e sua esposa ordenou a constru\u00e7\u00e3o da Ermida da M\u00e3e de Deus. Fez seu testamento na 1547/05/14 em favor de seu filho Gaspar  em 1546,  por promessa a Pedro Annes, agricultor, diz-se que este Pedro Annes residente na Faj\u00e3  era filho de Diogo Afonso Columbreiro, que j\u00e1 foi para Deus , em 1547/01/13, \u00e9 por isso que dizemos que o testamento n\u00e3o poderia ter sido feito no 1546, deveveria ter sido em maio de 1547 , \u00e9 f\u00e1cil  se confundir seis e sete nos scripts antigos. Dr. Ernesto do Canto, em seus estudos de Ermidas de S. Miguel, N. \u00ba 157 (Preto no Branco, p\u00e1g. 159) diz que  Afonso Diogo morreu  em 1547/01/13, no mesmo dia em que o testamento foi assinado como promessa. Quando ele morreu, apenas as paredes da Ermida da M\u00e3e de Deus  estavam construidas o resto da constru\u00e7\u00e3o foi conclu\u00eddo pela vi\u00fava e, sua filha Isabel.<br />\nDiogo Afonso e sua esposa foram enterrados entre o Cruzeiro da Matriz de Ponta Delgada, como est\u00e1 escrito no Testamento.<br />\nGeneral Notes: He Had made the construction of Madre de Deus Church  in Ponta Delgada, he was first a resident Vila Franca, after became resident in Ponta Delgada where he and his wife ordered the construction of the Hermitage of the M\u00e3e de Deus. Made his Will and Testament on the  14.5.1547 in favor to his son Gaspar or 1546, in the term of the Trusty Pedro Annes, farmer, it is said that this Pedro Anes resident in the Faj\u00e3 that it was of Diogo Afonso Columbreiro, that God already has, this was on the 13.1.1547, it is why we say that the testament could not have been in 1546 of that year because it must have been in May of 1547 and it is easy to see how one can get confused with six and seven in the old scripts.  Dr. Ernesto do Canto in his studies of Ermidas of S. Miguel, N.\u00ba 157 (Preto no Branco, p\u00e1g. 159)says that this  Diogo Afonso died on the 13.1.1547, in the same day that the Will was signed by the Trusty. When he Died only the walls of the Ermida of Mae de Deus was erected which was concluded by the widow and by his daughter Isabel.<br />\nDiogo Afonso e and his spouse were buried between the Cruzeiro of the Matriz of Ponta Delgada, as it is written on the Testament.\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
"<div>\n<i class=\"NoteType\">\nPerson Note\n</i>\n<div class=\"grampsstylednote\">\n<p>\nWas born in Portugal and served Prince Henry in Raposeira.He came to the Azores from Cani\u00e7o,Madeira and lived in Ponta Gar\u00e7a and Vila Franca.\n</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
